'''Workrave''' is a [[Free Software|free]] [[software application]] intended to prevent computer users from developing or aggravating [[occupational disease]]s such as [[carpal tunnel syndrome]], [[repetitive strain injury|repetitive strain injuries]], or [[myopia]].
The software periodically locks the screen while an animated character, âMiss Workraveâ, walks the user through various [[stretching exercises]],<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.freesoftwaremagazine.com/columns/workrave_combating_rsi_free_software_way |title = Workrave : combating RSI the free software way |author = Ryan Cartwright |work = [[Free Software Magazine]] |publisher = [[The Open Company Partners]] |date = 2008-05-28 |accessdate = 2008-08-24 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.linux.com/feature/119507 |title = Workrave fights repetitive strain injuries |author = [[David A. Harding]] |work = [[Linux.com]] |publisher = [[SourceForge, Inc.]] |date = 2007-10-03 |accessdate = 2008-08-24 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.oreillynet.com/onlamp/blog/2004/05/repetitive_software_injury.html |title = Repetitive software injury |author = [[Jono Bacon]] |work = O'Reilly ONLamp Blog |publisher = Blog of [[O'Reilly Media, Inc.]] |date = 2004-05-05 |accessdate = 2008-08-25 }}</ref> and urges them to take a [[coffee break]].
The program is [[cross-platform]], and dependent on the [[GTK+]] graphical [[widget toolkit]], and also on other [[GNOME]] libraries on [[Linux]].<ref name="devinfo" />
